article.headline: N. Dakota St. 65, Green Bay 61
article.story: FARGO, N.D. -- Mike Felt scored 17 points and Marshall Bjorklund had a double-double to help North Dakota State stay unbeaten with a 65-61 victory over Green Bay on Wednesday night. Bjorklund had 11 points and 13 rebounds while Lawrence Alexander scored 12 points with a game-best seven assists as the Bison (4-0) won their home opener. Alec Brown and Steve Baker scored 16 points apiece for the Phoenix (1-2). Dylan Hale sank two free throws that put North Dakota State ahead to stay 56-55 with 2:12 to go. Felt hit a 3-pointer and Taylor Braun sank a free throw to put the Bison up 60-55 with 1:07 left. Brown responded with three free throws to trim it to 60-58 with 36 seconds to play, but the Phoenix got no closer. The Bison were outrebounded 42-36 but forced 18 turnovers while committing only eight.
